**Critical**: Always filter out `message.sent` events to prevent infinite loops!
```python
@app.route('/webhook', methods=['POST'])
def webhook():
    event = request.json
    if event['type'] == 'message.sent':
        return 'OK', 200  # Ignore sent events!
    # Process message.received...
```

WebSockets provide real-time event streaming without polling:
```typescript
const client = new AsyncAgentMail();
const socket = await client.websockets.connect();
socket.subscribe({ inbox_ids: ["..."] });
socket.on('message.received', (event) => { ... });
```
Use WebSockets when you need instant notification; use webhooks for reliable delivery.
